Position Summary:
This position is responsible for full cycle talent acquisition activities and related projects in order to meet business development targets and people strategy at GCN level and in Central Hub.

Job Responsibilities:
1.R esponsible for full talent acquisition cycle from understanding hiring requirements from business lines, screen and search suitable candidates, implement interviews, negotiate and prepare offer proposals, and handle operational process to fulfill vacancies; 
2. Support for TA projects and keep good communication with project team;
3. Good cooperation with HRBP team to meet business lines' requirements and achieve people strategy targets; 
4. Implement employees' internal transfer, talent retention and exit process according to company's requirements; 
5. Keep updated TA related data and report;
6. Work together with HR team on improving existing working process and procedures.

Job Requirements:
1. Bachelor's degree or above;
2. Intern experience in HR filed;
3. Diligent, self-motivated and strong teamwork spirit;
4. Good communication and interpersonal skills;
5. Can work independently and efficiently; can work under pressure;
6. Good computer skill;
7. Good in English both written and verbal.
